parameters: \n<Kobold>\fs[\v[320]]\fn<\v[319]>Old Scale has guided our tribe since before the hairy ones came here!\.\. He was the wiser of us all...\fn<GameFont>\fs[30]
\n<Kobold>\fs[\v[320]]\fn<\v[319]>Hmph!\.\. You are friend with those hairy brutes,\. aren't you?!\fn<GameFont>\fs[30]
\n<Kobold Archer>\fs[\v[320]]\fn<\v[319]>Mind your manners around our Hive,\. kitten!\fn<GameFont>\fs[30]
\n<Kobold>\fs[\v[320]]\fn<\v[319]>Hmph!\.\. You are friend with those hairy brutes,\. aren't you?!\fn<GameFont>\fs[30]

\n<\n[1]>Hah...\.\.\. sneaking in wasn't too hard...\.\.\. let's see...\.\.\. what is this place?\.\.
Neneko approaches the cliff,\. looking over the edge.
The cat is taken aback as she gazes down the cliff. Down below,\. Neneko sees...\.\.\.
...\.\.\. A tribe of lizard-\.like people,\. short and dressed in rags and leathers.
Neneko tenses,\. her trained catlike eyes peering around as she crouches down,\. scouting the area.
\n<\n[1]>Damn,\. didn't think I'd just walk straight into the middle of enemy territory...\.\.\. gotta be careful...\.\.\.
She watches the Kobolds.\.\. This was a lot bigger than hunting monsters for food and cash. She needed to take her time...\.\.\.
The Kobolds down below go about their day,\. performing what looked like harmless errands and cheerfully yipping at each other.
\n<\n[1]>...\.\.\. Hey...\.\.\. aren't these guys...\.\.\. supposed to be monsters?\.\.
She watches as one seems to lead a bunch of rather passive looking giant lizards towards a river.
Another is carrying a pile of fruits and plants bigger than them towards the cliff.
Another is carrying a pile of fruits and plants bigger than them towards the cliff.
Neneko snarks,\. muttering.\.\. She's getting the feeling that the Dwarf Queen really was a bit biased with her description of these guys.
\n<\n[1]>They look like they're just minding their own business...\.\.\. Are they really at war with the dwarves?\.\.
She spots some patrolling guards and dips her head lower to hide along the cliff.
Bows and spears...\.\.\. seems like they do at least know how to fight.
Causing trouble around here'll definitely get some sharp objects sent her way,\. no matter how peaceful they looked.
\n<\n[1]>Something's up around here...\.\.\. Ruina said they had a Secret Way down to the Second Stratum...\.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Feels like I'm about to get dragged into other people's business again if I want to get anywhere...\.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Wonder if they'd be willing to talk...\.\.\. I'm definitely not a dwarf,\. so as long as Queenie over there was exaggerating about the trafficking thing,\. maybe...\.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>I can't make heads or tails out of their yapping...\.\.\. is there a way to communicate with these guys?\.\. If not,\. I doubt I can just go say hi...\.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Ugh,\. looks like I gotta figure things out.\.\. Let's get moving.
\n<\n[1]>I knew the critters and people down in the Hole were weirder than normal but I wasn't expecting THIS...\.\.\.
Neneko,\. curious,\. crouches down and observes the wandering lizards for a while.
She sees two small lizards scooping up water from the river nearby before running after each other towards a hole in the cliff face.
She guessed they all lived in caves,\. since there weren't any buildings.
There was another leading around some derpy looking big non-\.person shaped lizard,\. as if it were regular livestock.\.\. Maybe down here it really was?\.\.

All in all,\. despite the inhabitants,\. it looked like a regular,\. harmless little community.\.\. It looked pretty tight knit,\. too,\. with the lizards happily yapping at each other as they walked by.
\n<\n[1]>Looks peaceful...\.\.\. honestly,\. these guys look a lot happier than the people up above...\.\.\.
She dips her head as she spots some armed Kobolds,\. clearly on patrol.
\n<\n[1]>Guess they do have SOME defenses...\.\.\. they've got bows and spears,\. huh...\.\.\. really don't want to get stabbed at today...\.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>What are the chances they like outsiders?\.\.
She peers at the guards,\. twitching her ears.
\n<\n[1]>Mrgg...\.\.\. well,\. I'm not human,\. or look like those shorties at that fortress I passed by,\. so maybe that'll put me a bit higher in their books...\.\.\. still,\. better be careful.
\n<\n[1]>Don't feel like getting into a fight with a whole village today.\.\. That'll just be a waste of time...\.\.\.

\n<\n[1]>Right.\.\. I need info on this place if I want to get anywhere. These guys look peaceful,\. so maybe it'll be worth chatting them up and playing nice for now.\.\. They might know something...\.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>They're speaking some whole other lizard language.\.\. I don't have the time to learn how to yip and hiss...\.\.\. if I can't talk to them I might have to dig up info some other way...\.\.\.
Neneko gets up,\. brushing herself off.
\n<\n[1]>Alright,\. no time to waste,\. Nene. Let's get going!\.\.
\n<\n[1]>What you're doing in a place like this?\.\. ...\.\.\.\BST[5,Neneko] Wait,\. don't tell me...
\^\n<\n[1]>You felt left out?\.\. Wanted to join the kobolds now that you're a\.\.
\n<\n[3]>Continue,\. I dare you.\.\. "Now that I am a..."?
\n<\n[1]>Well...\.\.\. uh...\.\.\. you know...\.\.\. \BST[7]I didn't meant anything wrong by it!
\n<\n[1]>As you wish,\. like I want to get any close to that slimy tongue of yours!

Neneko pauses on her approach to the Kobold Village.\.\. There,\. she sees a short,\. green figure by the pond,\. one that she mistook at first for another kobold up until she looked at her clothes.\.\.

There's only one person she knows that wears an outfit like that.\.\. One who,\. last she'd seen of her,\. had experienced a case of spontaneous,\. mysterious green-\.ing...\.\.\. among other things.\.\.
\n<\N[3]>Why won't it come off...\.\.\. this mutation...\.\.\. could it have been from...?\.\.
Kaere,\. completely transformed,\. was crouched by the water,\. scrubbing at her arms with a desperation and fervor that Neneko felt like she might just scrub her skin off entirely.\.\.
\n<\N[3]>Fool...\.\.\. This is my fault...\.\.\. you're such a joke...\.\.\. this must be a side effect of that thing...\.\.\. why did you take it...\.\.\.
\n<\N[3]>They won't recognize me if I look like this...\.\.\. What will I do if I...\.\.\.
Kaere startles,\. flinching.\.\. Her head rises as she turns to look at Neneko,\. her new red and yellow eyes standing out from all the green around them as they stare at the cat.\.\.
\n<\N[1]>Surprised to see ya mingling with the kobolds.\.\. \BST[1,Neneko2]They accept you as one of their own or something now?\.\.
Neneko snarks,\. approaching Kaere.\.\. Kaere,\. however,\. flinches,\. standing up and taking a step back.\.\.
Kaere's sudden shout turns a few eyes towards the duo.\.\. The Kobolds don't seem particularly interested,\. though,\. and look away from the outsiders after a while.\.\.
\n<\N[1]>What,\. suddenly too good for me?\.\. \BST[3]You were real eager to get a lot closer to me before,\. ya know.\.\.
Kaere begins looking a bit flustered.\.\. Neneko is even certain she heard a hiss come out of her.\.\.
\n<\N[1]>Haaaah~\.\. Didn't take you for the type to kiss and run,\. ya know.\.\. What the hell was that anyway?\.\.
\n<\N[3]>...\.\.\. That...\.\.\. incident is exactly why you should keep your distance.\.\. \BST[2]For your own good.\.\.
Kaere looks down,\. her hands balling into fists,\. a look of frustration on her face.\.\.
\n<\N[3]>I...\.\.\. do not know if I can control this...\.\.\. this transformation.\.\. I've become some sort of beast.\.\.
\n<\N[1]>Now we have more things in common,\. yeah?~
\n<\N[3]>Tsk...\.\.\. that time,\. before...\.\.\. I wasn't in control of my actions.\.\. Foreign instincts have placed themselves in my mind...\.\.\.
Neneko tilts her head,\. taking a step forward.\.\.
\n<\N[1]>You look as sane and grumpy as always now,\. though?\.\. \BST[5,Neneko]Maybe it's out of your system now.\.\.
Kaere grimaces,\. crossing her arms.\.\. She hugs herself,\. looking away.\.\.
\n<\N[1]>It's not that bad.\.\. So you're green.\.\. Makes you stand out more.\.\. I think it's a good look on ya.\.\. Some kinda lizard...\.\.\. \BST[5]well,\. with that big tongue maybe a frog?\.\.
Neneko walks up to Kaere,\. eyes wandering around the shorter girl.\.\.
\n<\N[1]>You've even got a little tail now!\.\. Damn.\.\. \BST[4,Neneko]Actually,\. you're kind of cute like this,\. Kaere!\.\.
Kaere croaks in hostility,\. backing away from Neneko.\.\.
\n<\N[3]>Stop being so friendly!\.\. Being a beast may seem like it's normal to you,\. but I have a "normal" of my own!\.\.
\n<\N[3]>Do you understand?\.\. I am a human!\.\. I must...\.\.\. \BST[2]I must look like a human.\.\. Like me.\.\. I...\.\.\. There are people I must see again...\.\.\. how can I...\.\.\.
\n<\N[3]>How can I do that while looking like...\.\.\. like some freak?!\.\.
Neneko flinches.\.\. Kaere notices the look in the cat's eyes and makes a pained expression,\. but looks away soon after.\.\.
\n<\N[1]>Kaere,\. talk to me!\.\. We had a deal!\.\. After...\.\.\. everything before,\. we're finally both down here!\.\. We're a team,\. right?\.\.
[If Neneko knows about the further Layers]
\n<\N[1]>Kaere...\.\.\. this place goes deeper.\.\. This Stratum's just the first layer.\.\. I...\.\.\.
\n<\N[1]>What I'm looking for...\.\.\. it's not here.\.\. And whatever it is you're looking for won't be here either.\.\. Don't you get it?\.\.
\n<\N[1]>I have to...\.\.\. we have to go deeper down.\.\. \BST[3]We've gotta have each other's backs or no one else will!\.\.
\n<\N[3]>Neneko...\.\.\. this...\.\.\. I can't help you like this.\.\. I can't do anything like this.\.\. I...\.\.\. don't think I should have even come down here.\.\.
\n<\N[3]>I was foolish for thinking this would be within my abilities...\.\.\. \BST[2]That there wouldn't be any...\.\.\. dangers.\.\. That I would be unscarred.\.\.
\n<\N[1]>So,\. what,\. just cause things aren't easy you wanna call it quits?\.\. \BST[3]Nothing's easy,\. Kaere!\.\.
\n<\N[1]>Why is this so important to you,\. Kaere?\.\. It's pretty damn obvious that you followed me down here for your own reasons.\.\.
\n<\N[1]>And now suddenly you just want to give up!\.\. Because,\. what,\. you're a little stickier now?\.\.
Neneko stomps up to Kaere's face,\. glaring down at the frog girl.\.\.
\n<\N[1]>You know my secrets.\.\. You know exactly why I'm down here and why I'm not leaving.\.\.
\n<\N[1]>I think after every damn thing we've been through-\.\BST[3]-\. no,\. I've been through,\. going along with your plans it's time I know YOUR story.\.\.
\n<\N[1]>Tell me what's wrong,\. Kaere.\.\. Tell me why you came down here,\. why being human's so important.\.\.
\n<\N[1]>Depending on your answer,\. I'm either going to help you so we can keep moving,\. or kick your ass until you get your head back on straight so we can keep moving.\.\.
\n<\N[1]>Because like it or not,\. we're down in this stupid hole together,\. and I want your help.\.\. Got it?\.\.
Kaere shuts her eyes,\. looking down.\.\.
\n<\N[3]>...\.\.\. Alright.\.\. Alright.\.\. I will tell you.\.\.
She takes a deep breath,\. fidgeting her hands as she gathers herself.\.\.
Whatever Kaere was about to say was interrupted,\. as some sort of commotion began at the entrance to the village.\.\.
A Kobold,\. one that appeared to be in a sorry state,\. had run in,\. yipping in distress before practically collapsing on the spot.\.\.
The other Kobolds are immediately tense and up in arms.\.\.
It was true.\.\. The Kobold had a number of cuts and bruises,\. not to mention they looked exhausted.\.\. It looked like they had sprinted across the entirety of the Stratum.\.\.
The Kobold pants,\. yipping in a frenzy between gasps.\.\.
\n<Kobold>\fs[\v[320]]\fn<\v[319]>The queen is kidnapping kobolds...!\.\. I barely escaped...!\.\. There...\.\.\. there's still more prisoners in the fortress...!\fn<GameFont>\fs[30]
The Kobold's words have a clear effect on the surrounding Kobolds.\.\. They look outraged.\.\.
\n<\N[1]>Hey...\.\.\. \BST[7]everyone here's getting real dangerous...\.\.\. the hell's going on now...?\.\.
The injured Kobold has the full attention of the crowd,\. further riling them up.\.\.
It's enough that Neneko feels anxious,\. an outsider in the middle of a bunch of monsters that look ready for blood.\.\.
Those feelings are only justified when the injured Kobold's eyes land on Neneko and Kaere.\.\.
\n<Kobold>\fs[\v[320]]\fn<\v[319]>Those strangers...\.\.\. outsiders...!\.\. They can't be trusted...!\.\. Anyone could have come from that fake Queen...!\fn<GameFont>\fs[30]
Suddenly,\. all eyes turn towards the two non-\.Kobolds in the village.\.\.
\n<\N[3]>It's...\.\.\. better to be captured than to die fighting.\.\. There's too many and we're surrounded...\.\.\.
The cat and frog are both grabbed and restrained.\.\. Neneko struggles and growls at the little overconfident lizards,\. but Kaere hardly puts up a fight...\.\.\.
They're taken somewhere.\.\. Into the caves of the Kobold Village...\.\.\.
\n<Kobold Archer>\fs[\v[320]]\fn<\v[319]>Mind your manners around our Hive,\. kitten!\fn<GameFont>\fs[30]
\n<Perina>...\.\.\. Oh!\.\. It's you Neneko.\.\. Thank you for saving us back then!\.\. Gigi feels much better now...
\n<Perina>I know it's not much,\. but it was hard to stea...\.\.\. to get from the Fortress' treasury.\.\. \BST[1]Take this,\. it's just a trinket,\. for your help...
You can now tame a Gegerro!\.\. Feed one and get your friendly,\. sturdy,\. lizard!
\n<Kobold Archer>\fs[\v[320]]\fn<\v[319]>Mind your manners around our Hive,\. kitten!\fn<GameFont>\fs[30]
The huge Gegerro is lively,\. and seems to recognize the generous catgirl.
\n<Kobold>\fs[\v[320]]\fn<\v[319]>Kokoko!\.\. We are a peaceful tribe,\. it's those ugly dwarves that started snatching our eggs!\fn<GameFont>\fs[30]
